Two hrs algorithm to rule-in/ rule-out Acute Non-ST-Elevation Myocardial Infarction, measurement of HsTroponin-I:
Rule-out = < 2 ng/L
Rule-in = > 100 ng/L
Observational zone = 2 - 100 ng/L
Re-Test HsTn-I (two hrs after):  *[ Change < 6 ng/L = Rule- out]; * [Change > 10 ng/L = Rule-in]

For pulmonary embolism, the cutoff level is either 500 ng/mL, or age-adjusted as follows:
- < 50 years: 500 ng/mL
- >= 50 years: age x 10 ng/mL
(example: 650 ng/mL for 65 years)

Result interpretation: The test result should not be used as the sole criteria for the diagnosis of SARS-CoV-2 infections and based on CDC recommendation.

Symptomatic patients:
- Positive Antigen Test: Isolate/exclude from work
- Negative Antigen Test: Retest with PCR test immediately, isolate/exclude from work until PCR results are provided and proceed according to PCR test result.

Asymptomatic patients:
- Positive Antigen Test: Retesting by PCR test and patients should remain isolated in their rooms until PCR results are provided.
- Negative Antigen Test: No retesting is needed
